After millenia trapped in the Bleed, the Red Blade came to earth, where they battled earths defenders with the intentions to wipe out the human race and transform the planet in a new Khera. Kine personally engage in battle with Spartan and apparently killed him. She was killed by Majestic enraging her lover.

After being trapped in an drug deal busted by the WildCATs (and with the prime objetive to capture/recruit Ladytron), Lazarr was programed by TAO to obey him. Under his influence,, Lazarr put a bomb in the Clark's Bar, causing a more violent war in the post human community. But when Lazarr tried to escape, he ended trapped by a group of mercs as part of a hostage situation. Ladytron quickly identify him as the responsible of the bombing. When she captured him, Lazarr revealed her and the WildCATs about the duplicity of TAO.

deck: Joey is an rather runt-like man with an incredibly muscular right arm & a hand stuck inside a bowling ball. He's got a reputation for having little intelligence, because of this he uses brute strength in most of his conflicts.
description:
Origin

It is unknown when Joey the Ball became a gang leader; however, he appears to have a reputation throughout Lonely Street and with The Goon himself.

Creation

Joey the Ball was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume 1

After The Goon's bounty is raised to $50,000.00, Joey the Ball teams up with the Zombies to bring him in. Joey winds up ambushing The Goon and attacks him from behind, knocking him out with a single hit from his bowling ball. When The Goon awakens, Joey informs him of their partnership with the Zombies, this results in The Goon calling him an idiot for being so short sighted to realize that they're just using Joey as a pawn & will eliminate him when the time comes.

Joey refuses to believe this & leaves The Goon to be eaten alive by man-eating rats. When Joey goes to collect his bounty from the Zombie Priest things take a turn for the worse. Joey is about to be shot in the head by Lazlo but is spared, then knocked out, when The Goon arrives, miraculously alive after fighting "millions" of rats.

Equipment

Joey the Ball is always seen with his trademark bowling ball of which he uses in hand to hand combat quite often.

Abilities

Despite his small size and stature, Joey is rather agile and can leap large distances. He also has one incredibly muscular arm which he uses in tandem with his bowling ball to combat his foes.
name: Joey the Ball

deck: This Gigantic Zombie Chimp was once a normal chimpanzee; however, after being experimented on by the Zombie Priest he was turned into a 15-foot undead chimp.
description:
Origin

This creature was once a normal chimpanzee; however, he was captured by Lazlo and was brought to the Zombie Priest who turned him into a 15 foot, undead creature. Since then he became a weapon to be used by the Zombie Priest against The Goon and Franky

Creation

The Giant Zombie Chimp was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume 1

The chimpanzee was captured by Lazlo and brought to the Zombie Priest to be experimented on; the Zombie Priest claimed he was going to turn it into a gigantic 15 foot version of itself and make it a zombie. It is revealed later on that the Zombie Priest was successful, as the Giant Zombie Chimp arrives to battle The Goon when he bursts into the Zombie's hideout. Despite the Chimp's large size, The Goon prove to be too much for him, as he was hit in a weak point (his stomach), had his eyes gouged out by Goon's fists, and was blown up.

The Goon Volume 3

Due to his fight with 'The Goon' the Zombie Chimp was in miserable shape; having much of his body blown apart and his eyes gouged out. Thankfully for the Chimp, the Zombie Priest was able to bring him back to life, adding him once again to his undead army. The Zombie Chimp proved a fearsome foe in combat and was on the front lines when The Goon and his crew of Merle, Franky, Bruno, Dr. Alloy and the Mud Brothers attempted to rescue Buzzard. Dr. Alloy's robot servant, Bruno, wound up clashing with the Chimp to buy time for the others to escape. Unfortunately for both the Chimp and Bruno, Dr. Alloy activated Bruno's self-destruct sequence causing Bruno to explode, resulting in the apparent deaths of both him and the Chimp.

Powers & Abilities

The Giant Zombie Chimp is highly resistant to damage and was able to function after having it's stomach blown apart, this is due to it's undead nature. It is also incredibly strong and is far more aggressive than a normal chimpanzee.
name: Giant Zombie Chimp

deck: Former "friends" of The Goon & Franky, nearly killed in a trap set by Joey the Ball. Once their remains were sewn together by the Zombie Priest they became a single person.
description:
Origin

Frizt & Jocko used to be friends of The Goon and Franky but, after their "pals" sent them into a trap laid by Joey the Ball the friendship was destroyed, as were Fritz & Jocko's bodies. Using all the remaining pieces he could find, the Zombie Priest had them sewn together to create the disgusting man/zombie/creature known as Frizt & Jocko.

Creation

Fritz & Jocko were created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume 1

While The Goon & Franky are out trying to defeat some zombies they run into Frizt & Jocko; who has returned from the dead to defeat their former friends for leaving them to die in a trap set by Joey the Ball. Fritz & Jocko seem to have the upper hand in their fight before being interrupted by Fishy Pete. Eventually The Goon is able to defeat both Fishy Pete AND Frizt & Jocko, all thanks to Mickey Da Saw, a talking chainsaw used by The Goon. Using Mickey, The Goon saws off the head(s) of Fritz & Jocko and throws it/them in a trashcan.
name: Fritz & Jocko

deck: A member (and apparent leader) of the government group known as the G-Men. He makes a deal with the Zombie Priest in order to track down and capture The Goon.
description:
Origin

Of an unknown origin; he and the rest of his G-Men appeared out of the blue to aid the Zombie Priest catch The Goon.

Creation

G-Man Smith was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume 1

G-Man Smith and the rest of The G-Men appeared out of the blue to make an offer to the Zombie Priest that he couldn't resist, helping to catch the Goon in exchange for the identity of Labrazio. While searching for The Goon they find a graveyard with a headstone that has Labrazio's name on it, a clue for their investigation.

He and his G-Men later appear at the funeral of Brickhead Johnny, a former friend of The Goon. Johnny had been reanimated during his service and attacked The Goon, it was then learned that G-Man Smith had been working with Johnny as part of his plan to capture The Goon. Smith then interrogates The Goon and learns that Labrazio had been killed nearly 20 years ago by The Goon himself, however, he is quickly killed after this when The Goon escapes his restraints and stabs him in the skull.
name: G-Man Smith

deck: A con-artist who attempts to sell fresh brains to Zombies; his lies and deceit have given him a bad reputation with The Goon. He is also the manager of a club known as the Moonlight Firefly
description:
Origin

Wally's origin is never defined; however, he appears to have some sort of partnership with the Zombies as he's able to do business with them.

Creation

Wally was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume 1

Wally is down by the docks on Labrazio territory attempting to sell "fresh human brains" to a pack of zombies; however, he is interrupted by The Goon and Franky who expose his lies, as he was actually selling pig brains. The moment in which The Goon is about to beat him for his actions he calls upon Fritz & Jocko, his backup. During the fight that ensues Wally is able to escape.

The Goon Volume 2

Wally is found by The Goon backstage at Drakston Entity's magic show at the Moonlight Firefly, the performance space where Wally is manager. It is discovered that Wally tried to turn down Drakston due to not wanting a magic act in his club; however, Drakston used his magic abilities to make Wally seriously disfigured. The dis-figuration eventually led to Wally's death.
name: Wally

deck: A former friend of The Goon & Franky who was reanimated as a Zombie during his funeral service.
description:
Origin

Much of Johnny's life is left unknown; however, it was confirmed by Norton that he was killed by a pack of Zombies before he was reanimated.

Creation

Brick Head Johnny was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume 1

Not much was known about Brick Head Johnny before he was killed; however, Norton tells The Goon and Franky that Johnny was killed by a pack of zombies. Later on during Johnny's funeral service he is reanimated as a member of the undead and attacks The Goon & Franky, knocking Franky out and subduing The Goon long enough for The G-Men to arrive and help knock him out. It is learned that Johnny made a deal with the Zombie Priest that was just too good to resist; hence why he turned on his friend, The Goon.

The Goon: Color Special

After his fight with The Goon, Johnny had been hiding in the back of Smeagle's Bakery, having been hidden there for nearly two weeks. He was assaulted by The Goon & Franky after they found out his location, the duo still angry with him after their previous encounter. In an attempt to save his undead hide told the duo where the Matheson Coin Collection was hidden, asking that the two of them release him as payment due to their history as "pals". In response to this The Goon informed Johnny that he isn't going to be "pals" with no stinkin' zombie, he then shot Johnny in the head, killing him.
name: Brick Head Johnny

deck: A two-bit party magician who was cursed after finding a magical gem in the Lost Temple of Egroeg.
description:
Origin

Drakston Entity was originally a two-bit party magician who performed card tricks and slight hand. Eventually he stumbled upon a magical gem in the lost Temple of Egroeg (why he was there, the world may never know) and became cursed. He was given great power and could cast masterful illusions but was forced to provide human flesh for the gem's keepers, a duo of fierce harpies.

Creation

Drakston Entity was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume 2

Drakston Entity the Bizzarist made his way to the Moonlit Firefly to perform a dazzling magic show; it was here that he met Franky, friend of The Goon, who was attending the show with a date. Franky was chosen by Drakston's assistants and was cast away by a magical spell, Drakston then hypnotized the audience to make them forget that Franky had ever existed.

It had turned out that Drakston had attempted to kidnap Franky and planned on feeding him to his assistants, who were actually two harpies that were the protectors of the magical gem worn on Drakston's head. When confronted by The Goon Drakston confessed that he wasn't a murderer and that he had tried (but failed) to give the harpies an alternate food source.

In order for The Goon to save his friend and dispose of the harpies for good, he shattered the stone, killing Drakston & his harpies.

Powers & Abilities

Due to the magical gem he wears on his head, Drakston is able to conjure high level illusions, hypnotize large audiences and seemingly teleport.
name: Drakston Entity

deck: Samuel Loom is the thief who stole the Matheson Collection of 17th Century coins; a collection worth 8 million dollars. Unfortunately for him he was killed while burying the loot in the basement of the Decaster House.
description:
Origin

Loom's origin is largely unknown.

Creation

Samuel Loom was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Color Special

The story begins with Samuel Loom escaping with the Matheson Collection of 17th Century Coins, a collection he stole with an estimated worth of 8 million dollars. Deciding it'd be best to hide his loot and wait for police activity to die down, he ventured to the basement of the Decaster House, a seemingly haunted home with a twisted past. While burying his stolen coins a large wooden beam broke from the ceiling and landed on his back, pinning him to the ground. Unable to move, Loom was trapped for 5 days, eventually dying from starvation.
name: Samuel Loom

deck: The leader of a small gang of children who tormented Franky throughout his childhood.
description:
Origin

Nicky grew up in the same neighborhood as Franky and tormented him daily due to the clothes his mother forced him to wear. Due to Nicky's general "ruthlessness" he obtained a small following who aided him in his bullying ways.

Creation

Nicky was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume Three

A flashback tale reveals the first meeting of The Goon and Franky, who Nicky was bullying at the time. Unfortunately for Nicky, The Goon doesn't take kindly to bullies and beat the ever-living snot out of Nicky. Eventually Nicky tires to bully Franky once more; however, Franky has learned some new tips and tricks from his pal, The Goon, and is able to beat Nicky up in an act of self defense.
name: Nicky

deck: The King of the Hobos who live within the Hobo Jungle. He and those under his command are cannibalistic and attempted to eat The Goon & Franky.
description:
Origin

The origin of the King Hobo is unknown; though it can be assumed he once lived on Lonely Street.

Creation

The King Hobo was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume Three

The King Hobo addresses his subjects about their new captives, Houstus Grave, the Mongoloid Twins, Franky and The Goon. He talks with the Mongoloid Twins and frees them along with Houstus, deciding to eat The Goon & Franky. Unfortunately this was a mistake & the King Hobo is brutally beaten, it is unknown if he was killed or not.
name: King Hobo

deck: A lawyer type man who was hell-bent on preventing Dr. Alloy from being released from Cade's Maximum Security prison.
description:
Origin

Mr. Paterson is first seen as a member of the prison board advocating against the release of Dr. Alloy due to his history of mayhem and chaos. It is unknown what his life was like before becoming a member of the board.

Creation

Mr. Paterson was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume Three

Mr. Paterson is a member of the prison board that contains Dr. Alloy, a notorious villain of sorts who has terrorized the general public and the prison committee multiple times. The time has come to discuss if they should release Dr. Alloy into the public again or keep him locked up forever, and while Mr. Paterson is entirely against the idea of releasing him the other members of the board are willing to free him, sending Paterson into a tizzy.
name: Mister Paterson

deck: The owner of Paolo's barbershop; he owed a debt to Labrazio that was collected by The Goon & Franky.
description:
Origin

Much of Paolo's earlier life is unknown; however, at some point in his life he became an influential mobster who owed a debt to Labrazio. As a cover up for his operation he runs a simple barbershop.

Creation

Paolo was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume Three

When The Goon comes to his town he doesn't think much of it, laughing of the young man's attempts at reclaiming the debt owed to Labrazio. However; after his right hand man Renzo is killed and his corpse is hung in the middle of town he begins to take the threats more seriously. Paolo eventually comes to his senses and decides to pay his debt to the Goon, a decision that saved his life.
name: Paolo

deck: Paolo's right hand man; he was torn apart by zombies (and killed) when chasing after The Goon & Franky.
description:
Origin

Much of Renzo's earlier life is unknown; however, at some point he met Paolo and became his body guard.

Creation

Renzo was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume Three

When The Goon and Franky barge into Paolo's barbershop demanding that Paolo pay his debt to Labrazio; Renzo is tasked with tossing them out. Eventually Franky and The Goon return to the shop; however, they attempt to break in, a disturbance that alerts Renzo who begins to chase the two down. He chases them to a nearby building which is filled with zombies that then surround Renzo and tear him apart. Renzo's corpse is then hung in the center of town by The Goon & Franky to send a message to Paolo and the rest of his boys.
name: Renzo

deck: A thug who stole a safe full of naked Ingrid Bergman photos that belonged to The Goon & Franky. He was killed after The Goon threw him into a barrel of harpoons.
description:
Origin

Much of Leon's history is unknown, what is known is that at some point he stole a safe that belonged to The Goon and Franky, thus he became an enemy of theirs.

Creation

Leon was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume Three

After stealing a safe that belonged to The Goon & Franky, Leon finds himself in conflict with the Goon himself. The ensuing battle results in Leon being tossed onto a pile of harpoons, three of which stab him through the chest. Not willing to let the Goon have his safe back so easily, Leon kicks it into the ocean where it becomes guarded by an old sea hag.
name: Leon

deck: An old seafaring man who loans his diving equipment to The Goon.
description:
Origin

While much of Clancy's origin is unknown, he at one point began a diving service on Lonely Street.

Creation

Clancy was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume Three

After Leon tosses a safe belonging to The Goon and Franky into the sea, Clancy is called upon to loan the Goon some diving gear. Clancy warns the Goon about a legend that tells of a mysterious creature in the dark depths of the sea; however, his warnings are quickly dismissed. These warnings prove to be useful when the Goon comes across a sea monster that he combats and is able to escape from.
name: Clancy

deck: A mythical creature that slaughters chickens and is obsessed with pie. It also smells absolutely terrible.
description:
Origin

Boggy, the "horrible" Skunk Ape is the only live specimen to have been captured for display. It is unknown where or when Boggy was captured; but it is known as the chicken killing terror of five countries.

Creation

Boggy was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume Three

When Poachy brings his freak show to Lonely Street it raises quite a commotion, all because of the mysterious Skunk Ape he has with him. During one of the paid observations Boggy is able to escape and runs into the nearby city, causing chaos and discord throughout the town. When Boggy catches a hint of pie smell throughout the air it brings him to the local pie eating contest, it is here that he meets and enters a fight with The Goon. The two settle their differences after the Goon realizes he can satisfy the Skunk Ape's love for pie by entering it into the pie eating contest, thus allowing the Skunk Ape to devour tons of pie while simultaneously winning the Goon tons of money.
name: Skunk Ape

deck: A large lizard creature that resulted from an alien life form fusing itself with a Mexican Fire-Toad. It speaks only in Spanish and became a butler to Dr. Alloy after receiving several genetic modifications.
description:
Origin

A mysterious alien life form broke through the inter-dimensional barrier into the world of The Goon. Due to it's failure to acknowledge the customs and language of the new world it had entered, it began fighting with many of the inhabitants of Lonely Street. In the midst of a battle with the Goon this alien creature absorbed the essence of a Mexican Fire-Toad, transforming itself into the monster known only as Hombre Lagarto!

Creation

Hombre Lagarto was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume Three

Hombre Lagarto attacks Lonely Street and it's inhabitants only to be defeated by the Goon. This defeat allowed for Dr. Alloy to enter the fray and take the creature back to his laboratory where he would genetically modify the creature in order to create the perfect reptilian butler. Lagarto became Alloy's faithful servant; however, he would transform into his more feral state should he not receive his medication, an event that would occur several times, forcing the Goon to defeat the creature once more.

Powers & Abilities

Hombre Lagarto began as an alien from an unknown dimension; fusing his DNA with a Mexican Fire Toad he gained a scaly hide that is resistant to most blunt force attacks. Lagarto can change his size, growing more massive when he enters his feral states, and utilizes a combination of brute strength and incredibly sharp claws to attack his foes.
name: Hombre Lagarto

deck: A moronic simpleton who'd pop up on Lonely Street from time to time. He was usually seen with Franky and often creates "poo-art" with fecal matter.
name: Peaches Valentine

deck: He was a man looking to start up a professional football team when he stumbled upon The Goon. Together he and The Goon created the Fighting Fish-Canners; an incredibly successful football team that met an untimely demise at the hands of mobsters.

deck: An Inhuman who befriended Hellcat.
description:
Origin

Very little is known about Ian. Probably originally from New York, he is an Inhuman whose powers were activated when a spooky cloud messed him up.

Creation

Ian was created by Kate Leth and Brittany L. Williams. He made his first appearance in Patsy Walker, A.K.A. Hellcat! #1.

Major Story Arcs

Hellcat

Finding work increasingly hard to come by, Ian attempts to use his powers to rob an armoured car. He is stopped by Hellcat, but the pair bond and, after he agrees to return the money, become friends and roommates. He accompanies her on several adventures and, despite his reluctance to act as a hero, occasionally uses his powers to aid her.

Powers and Abilities

Ian is telekinetic, able to move objects with his mind at will. The exact strength and range of his telekinesis is unknown, but he does appear to be able to lift objects that are heavier than he could physically lift.
name: Telekinian

deck: She looks like Gwen Stacy and she's crazy like Deadpool. She is in fact Gwen Poole, aka Gwenpool. But she seem to have no ties with either of them!
description:
Origin

Gwen Poole came from a universe where all the Marvel stories are real comic books. Her background is, as of yet, unknown. It is however known that Gwenpool got transported into the real Marvel Universe by unknown means. Now she lives in the world and meets the heroes she only read about in her own world.

Creation

Gwenpool was created by Chris Bachalo, Christopher Hastings and Danilo Beyruth and first appeared in Howard the Duck Volume 4 issue 1. She had however appeared before on the variant cover of Deadpool's Secret Secret Wars issue 2 as part of the Gwen Stacy Variant Cover event. This cover was drawn by Chris Bachalo and proved to be so popular with fans that Marvel decided to give Gwenpool her own back-up stories in Howard the Duck and a special before granting her her own ongoing series.

Major Story Arcs

Into the Marvel Universe

Separated from her family, and being a fan of all of the heroes of the Marvel universe, and having read all of their comics, Gwen Pool now struggles to understand if this new universe is a fictional comic book or is real, while trying also to be a "superhero merc" to make some money.

Her whole "Pink Hydra Look" was the idea of a "superhero costume seller", who chose it manly inspired by her real name [Gwen Poole] and her hair-color [Pink].

Gwen Poole a.k.a. Gwenpool, seems to have no real superpowers, except for a vast Marvel universe knowledge from comic books in her universe [for example she knows every secret identity of heroes and criminals] and seems to be a fast learner. And a good "dimensional traveling survival experience"...

Other Media

Games

Marvel Future Fight

Gweenpool is a playable character in the game. She is a speed type, and her description in the game says: Gwen Poole was a comic book fan who was one day mysteriously transported into the Marvel Universe she had only read about in her own world. Under the impression that the Marvel Universe is all make-believe, she's taken on her own Super Hero identity to kick butt and have fun -- with zero consequences.

Marvel Contest Of Champions

Gwenpool in a playable character in the game. She is Skill Champion.

Marvel Puzzle Quest

Gwenpool is a playable character in the game.

Her bio in the game says: Now, this is a story all about how my life got...put...into...a Marvel game? Close enough. But also a lie. That story's a big secret. Very hush-hush. Super mystery #1.

Anyhow, have you seen this game? PARADISE FOUND, amirite? EVERYONE is here. Almost everyone. I touched Kamala Khan's hair. There are a few...exceedingly exasperating exceptions. I mean, I'll probably live. If you don't kill me. Can you even do that in this game? Don't kill me. Bye!
